A man is due to appear at the Mthatha Magistrate Court after he was found in possession of firearms, ammunition, drugs, and implements to commit a crime.The 47-year-old suspect was arrested on Thursday in an intelligence driven operation conducted by Crime intelligence, Mthatha K9 Unit and Vehicle Theft Unit at Viedgesville Locality in Mthatha.Eastern Cape provincial police spokeswoman Brigadier Marinda Mills said: &#8220;During the arrest firearms including a rifle with 35 rounds of ammunition, two 9mm pistols with 28 rounds of ammunition, a bolt cutter grinders and dagga were found.&#8220;Security company clothing, twelve Cellphones, twenty USB&#8217;s and three hunting knives were recovered.&#8221;-TNA Reporter 